(Title: A Minimal AI Study Assistant for Research Support) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Abstract:) Tj
T*
(This paper presents a lightweight AI study assistant designed for graduate students.) Tj
T*
(The system combines a large language model, simple agent task decomposition, and document retrieval.) Tj
T*
(Its goal is to help users understand papers, summarize academic content, and generate study plans.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Introduction:) Tj
T*
(Graduate students often need to read many research papers in a short time.) Tj
T*
(Traditional note-taking tools cannot answer questions based on uploaded documents.) Tj
T*
(A retrieval-augmented assistant can reduce reading time and improve research efficiency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Method:) Tj
T*
(The system first extracts text from uploaded PDF files.) Tj
T*
(Then the text is split into small chunks and converted into vector embeddings.) Tj
T*
(A FAISS index stores these vectors and retrieves the most relevant chunks for each user question.) Tj
T*
(The retrieved context is passed to a language model to generate grounded answers.) Tj
T*
(A simple rule-based agent decides whether the task is question answering, summarization, or study planning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Contributions:) Tj
T*
(First, the paper proposes a minimal architecture for an AI learning and research assistant.) Tj
T*
(Second, it integrates PDF parsing, vector retrieval, and language model answering in one Streamlit interface.) Tj
T*
(Third, it adds a simple agent that can decompose user tasks into summary, planning, and QA steps.) Tj
T*
(Fourth, the system is easy to extend with more advanced RAG and multi-agent capabilities.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Conclusion:) Tj
T*
(The prototype demonstrates that a small and clear system can support academic reading and learning tasks.) Tj
T*
(Future work will improve retrieval quality, add citation tracing, and support multiple documents.) Tj
T*
ET
